Name: ESRB Occasional Paper Series
Description: The ESRB Occasional Paper Series is an outlet for the publication of analytical and policy work that has been conducted within ESRB expert groups. The papers are typically written by ESRB Secretariat staff or the staff of ESRB member institutions, sometimes in collaboration with Advisory Scientific Committee members or external experts.
Any views expressed in occasional papers are those of the authors and do not necessarily reflect the official stance of the ESRB, its member institutions, or any institution to which the authors may be affiliated.
